title: Indonesia’s GoTo Braves Choppy Markets With $1.1 Billion IPO Plan
sub_head: Planned listing comes amid global market volatility, stoked by Russia’s invasion of Ukraine, elevated inflation
body:
Indonesia’s biggest startup filed to go public, seeking a valuation of nearly $30 billion in a deal that will test market appetite for new listings of emerging-market technology stocks.
GoTo Group offers ride-hailing, e-commerce and financial services in the world’s fourth-most populous nation, and counts Alphabet Inc.’s Google, Tencent Holdings Ltd. and Singapore’s Temasek Holdings among its backers.
